description: Devin Kraft is the artist and author of Dragon Slayer as well as several other self-published titles including The Devil and Dr. John, Deluge, Neverender, and The Ferryman. His style is equally as influenced by underground manga artists as is it is by contemporary western comic techniques. He currently lives in Dallas doing freelance illustration and design while he works on his next big comic project. You can see more of his art at his web site, or follow him on just about any social media network under the sun.
name: Devin Kraft

deck: A actress who portrays a young Storm in the X-Men film series.
description:
Biography

Alexandra Shipp is an American actress born and raised in Phoenix Arizona in 1991. She has been involved in acting since her youth, and eventually moved to Los Angeles to further pursue her career as an actress.

Acting Profile

Shipp has roles in television, including Days of Our Lives, Victorious and the television movie Aaliyah: The Princess of R&B. Movie roles include Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel, Straight Outta Compton and X-Men: Apocalypse.

Comic Movie Related Roles

Storm

Alexandra Shipp will play Storm in 2016's X-Men: Apocalypse. She is playing a "younger" version of the character, given its soft reboot nature, effectively taking over from prior Storm actress Halle Berry. Shipp's Storm references her comic characters history as a Cairo theft, and is used as an antagonist in this movie alongside Psylocke/Olivia Munn, Magneto/Michael Fassbender, and Angel/Ben Hardy as Horseman of Apocalypse. Shipp's Storm is the first modern mutant to be encountered by Oscar Isaac's reawakened Apocalypse.
name: Alexandra Shipp
